 **TESTING:**

In order to test this out, you should:

`docker-compose down --volumes`

Lift the docker environment and rebuild the newly created docker image:
`docker-compose up --build`

pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 449847785, 'comment_body': "Wow, so this was the issue! This explains why it failed, CMD from Dockerfile wasn't actually used but `command` from docker-compose was used instead! This means we'll need to also fix `containers/docker-compose-[stable|production].yml`", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 5, 8, 1, 49, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'icarito', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 449864806, 'comment_body': "I'm not 100% sure this part of the change is necessary. The idea was to let this run *without* affecting the running container so that any downtime is minimized.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 5, 11, 9, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'icarito', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 449937281, 'comment_body': 'Yes, this was overwriting the "original" CMD from Dockerfile.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 6, 0, 33, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alaxalves', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 449937643, 'comment_body': 'I removed it because the `rm` command is already executed in the `start.sh` file and the down cmd removal was a mistake :) (I removed it to debug). I switch run to exec because run cmd creates a new container instead of executing the desired commands in the plots2 container.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 6, 0, 36, 11, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alaxalves', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 449938660, 'comment_body': 'Quoting the discussion in Gitter:

"
Using docker-compose run forces the creation of a new container, thus running rake db:migrate && bundle exec rake assets:precompile ....... will create a new web container and run those commands there, instead of running those commands in the actual plots2 web container
"', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 6, 0, 45, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alaxalves', 'type': 'User'}]
